UBS Hires Innocenzi as CEO for Italian Wealth Management Unit

-- B y   E l i s a   M a r t i n u z z i
-- 
2011-10-03T09:22:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-03/ubs-hires-innocenzi-as-ceo-for-italian-wealth-management-unit.html
UBS AG (UBSN)  said it hired  Intesa Sanpaolo
SpA (ISP) ’s Fabio Innocenzi as chief executive officer of its Italian
wealth management unit.  Innocenzi, 50, succeeds Ferruccio Ferri and his appointment
is effective on Nov. 1, according to an e-mailed statement
today. At Intesa, Innocenzi oversaw the bank’s units in north-
eastern Italy.  Ferri is becoming chairman of UBS’s Italian fiduciary unit
after a year in which UBS boosted sales and net new assets at
the wealth management division, according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elisa Martinuzzi in Milan at 
 emartinuzzi@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Edward Evans at   eevans3@bloomberg.net  